This paper deals with the geometry and topology of polyhedra, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concept of unfolding a polyhedron without overlap is also relevant to the field of geometric rigidity theory (cs.GR). Additionally, the use of grids and refinement is a common technique in computational science (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS).
